parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often when the driver is braking or shifting gears. The accelerator pedal may be depressed
and the vehicle may continue to accelerate even when the driver tries to brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The brakes fail to slow down or stop the vehicle
even when the brake pedal is depressed. The ABS system may be activated
but the vehicle may not slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission issues can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal may feel soft or spongy
and the vehicle may accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly. The transmission may slip or hesitate
causing the vehicle to lose power or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electronic throttle control issues can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The engine may race or rev suddenly
and the vehicle may accelerate unexpectedly. The cruise control may malfunction
causing the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: None
as the airbag did not deploy in the reported incidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The recall of Takata airbags has led to a shortage of replacement parts, leaving vehicles with potentially defective airbags on the road, which can cause serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: None
as the complaints are related to the recall process and availability of replacement parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
jumps a curb
and crashes into an object.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the engine to stall while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine warning light illuminates
the engine starts but some electrical components do not function
the vehicle stalls while driving at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shut-off of the vehicle when the brake pedal is depressed can cause accidents, especially at red lights or intersections.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off when the brake pedal is depressed
requiring the driver to turn the vehicle off and on to drive properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power steering, and experience intermittent electrical issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The instrument cluster flickers
various internal and external lights randomly illuminate
the power steering fails
the steering wheel becomes extremely tight
and the vehicle stalls multiple times without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering system failure can cause the vehicle to drift or pull to one side, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle drifts severely to one side
especially at high speeds
and requires constant pressure on the steering wheel to maintain control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress can cause electrical system failures, leading to loss of power steering, stalling, and other safety issues.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences electrical system failures
such as the battery light coming on and loss of steering
after driving through water.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is unable to be stopped or controlled.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly without input from the driver
the brakes are depressed to the floor without effect
the vehicle continues to accelerate rapidly
shifting to neutral does not stop the acceleration
the vehicle slows down or stops only when placed in reverse or park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down in time.
symptoms: The brake pedal will not depress or has a delayed response
the vehicle continues to move forward even when the brakes are applied
the brake pedal has to be pumped to engage
the vehicle "bucks" or jerks when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent brake failure can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down in time.
symptoms: The brake pedal will not depress or has a delayed response intermittently
the vehicle continues to move forward even when the brakes are applied intermittently
the brake pedal has to be pumped to engage intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electronic throttle control system failure can lead to sudden unintended acceleration, accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly without input from the driver
the throttle body inspection reveals no abnormalities
the computer codes show no abnormalities.
